//! PRN (Penetrating Regulatory Node) Compliance Adapter
//!
//! This module provides the compliance layer for the BIS Unified Ledger
//! integration. It connects to the JMBC PRN (Penetrating Regulatory Node)
//! network to perform real-time AML/CFT checks, sanctions screening, and
//! generates immutable audit logs (PRNAUDIT RR) for regulatory reporting.
//!
//! # Architecture
//!
//! The compliance adapter acts as a bridge between the BIS Unified Ledger
//! and the PRN network. It ensures that all transactions are checked against
//! regulatory rules before settlement, and maintains an immutable audit trail
//! that can be used by regulators for post-hoc analysis.
//!
//! # PRNAUDIT RR
//!
//! The adapter generates PRNAUDIT RR records that form an immutable hash chain
//! of all compliance events. Each entry includes:
//! - Transaction identifier
//! - Event type and data
//! - Previous hash (chaining)
//! - Ed25519 signature for non-repudiation
//!
//! # References
//! - PRN Security Framework (JMBC)
//! - FATF Recommendations for AML/CFT
//! - IETF draft-guorong-utxo-dns-01 – PRNAUDIT RR specification

use std::collections::HashMap;
use serde::{Deserialize, Serialize};
use reqwest::Client;
use thiserror::Error;

